25|$|Quong Tart's tea {{rooms were}} also located at 777 George St, in Moore Park Zoo, {{and in the}} Haymarket theatre district. They were the site of Sydney's first suffragette meetings, and between 1885 and 1888, were home to {{functions}} for inmates of destitute asylums. As part of his employment program, he devised new policies for his employees, including sick leave, <b>holiday</b> <b>pay</b> and time off for personal reasons.|$|E
