50|$|Between 1926 and 1950, Galloway lived {{mainly in}} the town of Cluj, Romania. He worked for the Ethnographic Museum of Transylvania in Cluj between 1927 and 1929, {{spending}} periods of 5 to 6 months in different ethnographic areas of Transylvania. He painted watercolours of traditional rural <b>holidays,</b> <b>paying</b> particular attention to the finer details of traditional folk costumes. He collected ethnic objects and took photographs in the Kalotaszeg region, in Piladureni, Hațeg and in the Banat region. which were donated to the museum in 1927.|$|R
